TITLE: Billionaire Stephen Deckoff buys Jeffrey Epstein's private islands
SUMMARY: Jeffrey Epstein used his private retreat in the U.S. Virgin Islands to sexually abuse multiple women. A billionaire plans a new luxury resort there.

TITLE: The market is looking for the next 'domino' to fall, keeping banks under pressure
SUMMARY: The sharp selloff in regional banks sparked by the March failure of Silicon Valley Bank resumed Tuesday, catching Wall Street analysts and investors off guard.

TITLE: Apple expected to announce $90 billion in buybacks and dividends when it reports earnings
SUMMARY: Regardless of its quarterly results, Apple will remind investors of how much cash it generates and its extreme profitability.

TITLE: Qualcomm gives light forecast, phone chip sales fall 17%
SUMMARY: Qualcomm reported second-quarter earnings on Wednesday that saw sales from handset chips, a core business for the company, decline.

TITLE: Top banking CEO warns of further volatility and predicts more U.S. rescues
SUMMARY: A top banking executive said he expects more American banks to be rescued after JPMorgan stepped in to buy First Republic.

TITLE: Deposition of JPMorgan CEO Dimon in Jeffrey Epstein lawsuit set for late May, source says
SUMMARY: Jeffrey Epstein, a sex offender who had been friends with Donald Trump and Bill Clinton, was a customer of JPMorgan Chase for years.

TITLE: That simple 'hi' text from a stranger could be the start of a scam that ends up costing you millions
SUMMARY: "Pig butchering" operations run out of Asia but target victims globally, with scammers promising love and wealth to get their victims to invest their fortunes.

TITLE: Chegg shares rebound with 17% pop after losing almost half their value on ChatGPT concerns
SUMMARY: Chegg CEO Dan Rosensweig told CNBC late Tuesday that the stock's 48% plunge during regular trading hours was "extraordinarily overblown."

TITLE: Ford restores faith with quarterly results, while Starbucks proves to be a China play
SUMMARY: Club holding Ford (F) on Tuesday showed investors it had righted the ship in the first quarter, while Starbucks' (SBUX) quarterly sales were bolstered by China.

TITLE: After First Republic's rescue, economists predict further pain with a 'new era' of higher inflation
SUMMARY: Turmoil in the banking sector means central banks face in increasingly "delicate dance" in their efforts to rein in inflation, World Economic Forum Managing Director Saadia Zahidi told CNBC.

TITLE: South Korea's finance minister says country is at a 'turning point' in relations with Japan
SUMMARY: South Korea's finance minister says the nation sees a "turning point" in economic relations with Japan.

TITLE: Jeep, Dodge maker Stellantis posts first-quarter revenue jump as chip supply eases
SUMMARY: Carmaker Stellantis on Wednesday posted a 14% annual rise in first-quarter net revenues as an easing of semiconductor supply chain pressures boosted shipments.

TITLE: These are the top 10 most in-demand job skills right now, according to the World Economic Forum
SUMMARY: As jobs are going through a transformational time, the World Economic Forum lays out the top 10 most important skills for workers, and how they'll shift.

TITLE: Eli Lilly Alzheimer’s treatment donanemab slowed disease progression in clinical trial
SUMMARY: Donanemab, a monthly antibody infusion made by pharmaceutical company Eli Lilly, also significantly reduced brain plaque associated with Alzheimer's disease.

TITLE: Bank of Korea governor says it's 'premature' to talk about rate cuts
SUMMARY: "It would be a little bit premature to talk about pivot at this moment," Bank of Korea Governor Rhee Chang-yong told CNBC.

TITLE: India's ties with Russia remain steady. But Moscow's tighter embrace of China makes it wary
SUMMARY: Moscow has also grown close to Beijing since invading Ukraine, and that raises critical national security concerns for New Delhi.

TITLE: AMD revenue drops 9% as PC chip sales decline sharply
SUMMARY: AMD's report comes as the PC industry is in a deep slump, with shipments dropping 30% in the first quarter, according to IDC.

TITLE: Starbucks earnings beat as China reverses same-store sales declines
SUMMARY: Starbucks said its same-store sales climbed 11% in its fiscal second quarter.

TITLE: Michael Milken says recent crisis is the same mistake banks have been making for decades
SUMMARY: Famed investor Michael Milken said the current banking crisis stemmed from a classic asset-liability mismatch that had played out miserably time and again.

TITLE: Hindenburg Research goes after Carl Icahn in latest campaign for market-moving short seller
SUMMARY: The Nathan Anderson-led firm took a short position against Icahn Enterprises, alleging "inflated" asset valuations, among other reasons.

TITLE: Ford posts stellar first quarter, boosted by fleet and legacy truck divisions
SUMMARY: Ford is reporting its quarterly financial results by business unit, instead of by region, for the first time.

TITLE: Hollywood writers are on strike — here's what it means for TV and movie production
SUMMARY: Writers are seeking more compensation to reflect the content boom driven by streaming over the past several years.

TITLE: Wall Street is cutting more jobs as Morgan Stanley plans 3,000 layoffs
SUMMARY: For Morgan Stanley and others, the cuts show Wall Street is wrangling with a slump that's dragging on for longer than expected

TITLE: Tesla hikes prices in U.S., China and other markets after multiple cuts
SUMMARY: Tesla increased the price of vehicles including its Model 3 and Model Y in the U.S., China, Canada, and Japan.

TITLE: IMF raises 2023 economic outlook for Asia, sees China and India making up half of global growth
SUMMARY: The International Monetary Fund said Asia-Pacific growth will primarily be driven by China's recovery and "resilient" growth in India as the rest of the world braces for slowed growth.

TITLE: Drugs, guns and crypto seized, 288 arrested, in 'unprecedented' dark web crackdown
SUMMARY: Operation SpecTor took down the darknet site Monopoly Market and resulted in the arrests of 288 suspects who sold drugs and other goods for crypto.

TITLE: Chegg CEO calls 48% stock plunge over ChatGPT fears 'extraordinarily overblown'
SUMMARY: Chegg's stock was almost halved on Tuesday after CEO Dan Rosensweig warned that OpenAI's ChatGPT was "having an impact" on customer growth.

TITLE: Samsung bans use of A.I. like ChatGPT for employees after misuse of the chatbot
SUMMARY: Samsung confirmed on Tuesday that it is temporarily restricting the use of generative AI products, such as ChatGPT, through the company's personal computers.

TITLE: Nearly 25% of jobs are set to be disrupted in the next five years — and A.I. could play a key role: World Economic Forum
SUMMARY: WEF expects there to be 14 million fewer jobs overall in five years' time as labor markets face an overhaul from AI and a slew of other factors.

TITLE: PacWest falls more than 20% as regional bank stocks slide to new lows
SUMMARY: Regional bank stocks saw their losses for the week deepen as investors digest the failure of First Republic.
